  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the relatively modest amount of $25,000 and the fact that restitution has already begun to be made mitigate the need for a lengthy prison sentence. A term of 6 months is sufficient to serve as both a deterrent and a recognition of the severity of the offense while allowing for potential rehabilitation and continued repayment of the stolen funds.",
  "verdict": 6
}
